<div><a style="display: none;"></a><span style="cursor: pointer;">Levelling Methods for Paladins</span></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler">
<div style="font-size: x-large; color: #0077ff; text-align: left;"><span style="color: #0047ff; font-family: 'comic sans ms';"><strong style="font-size: -webkit-xxx-large; text-decoration: underline;">Leveling Guide</strong><br /><br /><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong>Here I will explain to you the methods of how most of us paladins leveled from 140-350 via exp quests or through hardcore grinding. Feel free to select whichever methods are easier and more of your preference.</strong></span></span></div>
<div style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: 'comic sans ms';"><br /><span style="font-size: 300%; color: #0047ff; font-weight: bold;">Grinding:<br /></span><br /><span style="color: #20ca5d; font-size: xx-large;"><strong>Baum Warriors [240+]<br /></strong></span><br /><strong><span style="color: #20ca5d;"><span style="font-size: x-large;">Location:</span><br /><span style="font-size: medium;">Kilf Rocky Area<br /><br /></span><span style="font-size: x-large;">Attribute:</span><br /><span style="font-size: medium;">Earth<br /><br /></span></span><span style="color: #20ca5d; font-size: x-large;">EXP Gain (Non-Ticket) Solo-Wise:<br /></span><span style="color: #20ca5d; font-size: medium;">193-194k Experience<br /></span></strong><br /><img style="max-width: 100%;" src="https://i.imgur.com/916m1pA.jpg" alt="" /><br /><span style="color: #20ca5d; font-size: x-large;">Another high HP mob which is a great proceed from Nommars and Megaroches. These mobs have about 7 times as much HP as Megaroches do, so taking them down will be quite the challenge. Fire Element weapons will be great against taking these monsters down. I also would recommend joining a party since it will be quite tedious farming with Guardian until you get Knight's Oath. Parties would definitely love someone to take the hate whilst they're free to do damage.<br /><br /></span><span style="color: #b30373; font-size: xx-large;"><strong>Yardes [260+]<br /></strong></span><br /><strong style="color: #b30373;"><span style="font-size: x-large;">Location: </span><br /><span style="font-size: medium;">Zalms Plains<br /><br /></span></strong><span style="color: #b30373; font-size: x-large;"><strong>Attribute:<br /></strong></span><span style="color: #b30373; font-size: medium;"><strong>Light<br /><br /></strong></span><strong style="color: #b30373;"><span style="font-size: x-large;">EXP Gain (Non-Ticket) Solo-wise:<br /></span><span style="font-size: medium;">325-327k Experience<br /></span></strong><br /><span style="color: #b30373;"><img style="max-width: 100%;" src="https://i.imgur.com/B6yrNPn.jpg" alt="" /></span><br /><span style="color: #b30373; font-size: x-large;">These mobs offer almost double the amount that Baum Warriors do. Not only this, but they have just about the same HP as Baum Warriors, just a little more. Again, I would recommend getting a PT as it will be tedious since these mobs have 7-8x times the HP than the mobs back in EP2. If you have Knight's Oath, however, it should be a fun farm as it is an AoE skill and these mobs do not put ailments on you often. What is even more amazing is that this mob is part of a quest from Chat called [Secure the Transport Path!] where it is optional to kill 10 of these baddies, and you will get 380% more than you normally would from the quest. A great grind, indeed!<br /><br /></span><span style="color: #ff00ff; font-size: xx-large;"><strong>Third Eyes [300+]<br /><br /></strong></span><span style="color: #ff00ff; font-weight: bold; font-size: x-large;">Location:</span><br /><span style="color: #ff00ff; font-weight: bold; font-size: medium;">Tower of Yafula<br /><br /></span><span style="color: #ff00ff; font-weight: bold; font-size: x-large;">Attribute:<br /></span><span style="color: #ff00ff; font-weight: bold; font-size: medium;">Neutral<br /><br /></span><span style="color: #ff00ff; font-weight: bold; font-size: x-large;">EXP Gain (Non-Ticket) Solo-Wise:<br /></span><span style="color: #ff00ff; font-weight: bold; font-size: medium;">480K Experience<br /><br /><img style="max-width: 100%;" src="https://i.imgur.com/NUP2Zwo.jpg" alt="" /><br /></span><span style="color: #ff00ff; font-size: x-large;">This is the latest high HP mob that offers the most EXP of all the mobs in Iruna. It is also the most frequently visited area for grinding as of far. These mobs spawn very uncommonly and have a high amount of HP (1,000,000). You should totally go here if you want the best possible results EXP wise. I absolutely recommend a PT as these mobs are very hard hitting unlike the other ones covered.<br /><br /></span><span style="color: #00a2a8; font-size: xx-large;"><strong>Nommars [240+]<br /></strong></span><br /><span style="color: #00a2a8;"><span style="font-size: x-large;"><strong>Location:<br /></strong></span><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong>Primordial Lands<br /><br /></strong></span></span><strong><span style="color: #00a2a8;"><span style="font-size: x-large;">Attribute:<br /></span><span style="font-size: medium;">Fire<br /><br /></span></span></strong><span style="color: #00a2a8; font-size: x-large;"><strong>EXP Gain (Non-Ticket) Solo-Wise:<br /></strong></span><span style="color: #00a2a8; font-size: medium;"><strong>84K Experience<br /><br /><img style="max-width: 100%;" src="http://s6.postimg.org/bfdykzg6p/Screenshot_2015_04_02_12_31_51.png" alt="" /><br /></strong></span><span style="color: #00a2a8; font-size: x-large;">This is a great mob to do and I would recommend this before Baum Warriors. Why? Because it has two quests for you to do for your enjoyment. Not only this, but it seems that it is rare to see a lot of people here grinding. It is a wide open space for everyone to have fun. Their spawn is not uncommon and you will usually find yourself killing 2-3 of these each time around. You're free to try this one solo as these mobs are not hard hitting but they may be a bit annoying as they have the tendency to stun you. If you're going to try this mob out, getting the [Dirty Gears] quest in Pilaneza City is a must as you will collect these as you grind. Getting the other one [Monsters in Holy Lands] is optional as you only have to kill 5 Nommars for this quest. You won't see yourself coming to kill alot of Nommars if you do, but you will be rewarded a good chunk of EXP for your efforts.</span><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-size: x-large; color: #35a700; font-weight: bold;"><span style="font-size: xx-large;">Megaroche [160+]<br /></span><br /><span style="font-size: x-large;">Location:</span><br /><span style="font-size: medium;"> Mubele Pass</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: x-large;">Attribute:</span><br /><span style="font-size: medium;"> Water</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: x-large;">Exp Gain (Non-Ticket) Solo-wise:</span><br /><span style="font-size: medium;">149-151K Experience<br /><br /></span></span><strong style="font-size: x-large; color: #0077ff;"><img style="max-width: 100%;" src="http://s6.postimg.org/6jabtag1d/Screenshot_2015_04_02_11_46_13.png" alt="" /></strong><br /><span style="font-size: x-large; color: #35a700;">These are one of the high HP mobs where everyone grinds usually. I wouldn't recommend soloing these as they have high hp, and you will end up burning up alot of pots. Exp within a 4 man party will probably be cut down to 60-80K Experience, but even so its good exp if you don't like doing Exp quests. I'd recommend doing this if you like to party up with people, which you should be doing since you are a pally anyways xD. This will feel slow early on in my opinion since megaroche are always crowded with players . Use wind element weapons like sinbad or have an enchanter cast wind origin on you if you'd like to deal more guardian damage due to elemental advantage.&nbsp;</span><br /><br /><strong style="font-size: x-large; color: #0077ff;"><span style="color: #f15106;"><span style="font-size: xx-large;">High Ent [160+]</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: x-large;">Location:</span><br /><span style="font-size: medium;">Magonza's Fortress </span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: x-large;">Attribute: </span><br /><span style="font-size: medium;">Fire</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: x-large;">Exp Gain (Non Ticket) Solo-wise: </span><br /></span><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="color: #f15106;">37K Experience</span><br /><br /></span></strong><span style="font-size: x-large; color: #35a700;"><img style="max-width: 100%;" src="http://s6.postimg.org/61f6dfqgh/Screenshot_2015_04_02_12_02_03.png" alt="" /></span><br /><span style="font-size: x-large; color: #ee6900;">This is another fairly high Hp mob you will find everyone grinding usually now. Since these mobs don't have as high hp as megaroche, I would recommend trying to solo these since they are fairly easy to kill. In a 4 man party your exp will probably be cut down to around 10-25K at the minimum, but because they are easy to kill it may be faster rather than to do megaroche. However this area is crowded as well but the spawn rate for high ents are faster than megaroche. Use fire elemental weapons to increase your guardian damage such as Dragon roar due to elemental advantage or have an enchanter cast fire origin on you.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: x-large;"><span style="color: #7e9600;"><strong><span style="font-size: xx-large;">Balor [160+]<br /></span></strong><br /><strong><span style="font-size: x-large;">Location: </span><br /><span style="font-size: medium;">Halib Marshlands</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: x-large;">Attribute: </span><br /><span style="font-size: medium;">Water</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: x-large;">Exp Gain (Non Ticket) Solo-Wise:</span><br /></strong></span><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong><span style="color: #7e9600;">98-101K Experience</span><br /></strong></span></span><br /><span style="font-size: x-large; color: #0077ff;"><img style="max-width: 100%;" src="http://s6.postimg.org/vo1c6pfht/Screenshot_2015_04_02_12_24_58.png" alt="" /></span><br /><span style="color: #7e9600; font-size: x-large;">This is one of the high HP mobs you may find some people grinding usually. I wouldn't recommend soloing these as they have higher HP than high ents, so you will end up burning through alot of pots to kill one, although they don't have as high hp as a megaroche. In a 4 man party you will gain around 45-60K experience. This area isn't as crowded as Megaroche or High ents, so it would be good if you can manage to form a party here as Balors spawn on all floors of this dungeon. Use wind elemental weapons like Sinbad to increase your guardian damage against these mobs due to elemental advantage or have an enchanter cast wind orgin on you</span><span style="color: #7e9600; font-size: x-large;">.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: x-large; color: #048097;"><span style="font-size: xx-large;"><strong>Amikiri [140+]<br /></strong></span><br /><strong><span style="font-size: x-large;">Location:</span><br /><span style="font-size: medium;">Eccentric's Manor</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: x-large;">Attribute:</span><br /><span style="font-size: medium;">Dark&nbsp;</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: x-large;">Exp Gain (Non Ticket) Solo-Wise:</span><br /></strong><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: medium;">4.8-4.9K Experience&nbsp;</span><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: medium;"><img style="max-width: 100%;" src="http://s6.postimg.org/6fgid1ak1/Screenshot_2015_04_02_11_27_24.png" alt="" />&nbsp;</span><br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;">These are one of the low level mobs you will find early on to grind till you have guardian. These mobs have really low hp so I would recommend soloing these if you are below 160 and want to work your way up to getting guardian. To top it all off these mobs are dark element, meaning that you can abuse them with gloria buff (yay xD) and spam hard hit or holy thrust against them. I would strongly recommend to level with these mobs if you don't enjoy doing exp quests.&nbsp;</span></span><br /><span style="font-size: x-large; color: #0047ff; font-weight: bold;"><br /></span></span><hr style="font-size: x-large; color: #0077ff;" /><span style="font-size: x-large; color: #0077ff; font-family: 'comic sans ms';"><span style="color: #0047ff; font-weight: bold;"><br /></span></span><span style="font-size: x-large; color: #0077ff; font-family: 'comic sans ms';"><span style="color: #20ca5d;"><span style="font-size: 300%;">Quests:</span><br /><span style="font-size: x-large;"><strong>For quests, refer to this&nbsp;<a href="http://irunaonline.boards.net/thread/26925/quest-guide" target="_blank" rel="noopener norewrite">guide</a>&nbsp;here. Any quest is great for a Paladin to take.</strong></span><br /><br /></span><br /><br /><br /></span></div>
</div>
