<div data-tag="spoiler"><span style="color: #0077ff;">{Skill Descriptions and Requirements}</span><span style="font-family: 'comic sans ms';"><span style="font-size: medium;"><strong style="color: #0077ff;"><span style="color: #f70000;">Defense (Passive) - Offers a permanent gain to DEF, protecting you from attack.</span></strong><br /><strong style="color: #0077ff;"><span style="color: #0047ff;">SLv6 - Obtained from the Class Change from Apprentice Paladin to Paladin.</span></strong><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #fd0000;">Heal (Active) - Recovers the target's HP.</span></strong><br /><strong style="color: #0077ff;"><span style="color: #0047ff;">SLv1 - Obtained from the Class Change from Apprentice Paladin to Paladin.</span></strong><br /><br /><strong style="color: #0077ff;"><span style="color: #f70000;">Resist (Passive) - A permanent boost to Magic Defense.</span></strong><br /><strong style="color: #0077ff;"><span style="color: #0047ff;">SLv1 - Obtained from the Class Change to Apprentice Paladin.<br />SLv2 - Obtained from the Class Change to Paladin.<br />SLv3 - Obtained from a Lv.260 Book from Sitara in Kleya City.</span></strong><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #fd0000;">Guard (Passive) - Defense the target against attacks, reducing HP Damage.</span></strong><br /><strong style="color: #0077ff;"><span style="color: #0047ff;">SLv2 - Obtained from the Class Change to Paladin.</span></strong><br /><br /><strong style="color: #0077ff;"><span style="color: #f70000;">Provoke (Active) - Provoke and anger your foe, making you the target of future attacks. (I believe this description is not explained correctly, it raises your hate bar by a considerable amount rather than actually making you the target.</span></strong><br /><strong style="color: #0077ff;"><span style="color: #0047ff;">SLv4 - Obtained from a Lv.140 Skill Book from King Elbano in Capital City Elban after the class change to Paladin.</span></strong><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #fd0000;">Gloria (Active) - Raises light element attack power for a period of time.</span></strong><br /><strong style="color: #0077ff;"><span style="color: #0047ff;">SLv1 - Obtained from the Class Change to Paladin.</span></strong><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #fd0000;">Parry (Passive) - A skill to parry the enemy's attack. Chance of reducing melee damage. It reduces more by Swords. (This is disabled for 5 seconds after activated)</span></strong><br /><strong style="color: #0077ff;"><span style="color: #0047ff;">SLv1 - Obtained from the Class Change to Paladin.<br />SLv2 - Obtained from a Lv.200 Skill Book from Matif in Drafbourg: Immigrant Ward.<br />SLv3 - Obtained from a Lv.260 Quest from Delma in Lograth City. You must:</span><br /><span style="color: #00ac00;">-Kill 60 Miedo Colons (Ireve Ruins) and Piglets (Rosana Highlands)<br />-Collect 8 Strong Metals (Peltas, Heavy Armored Knights' Fortress) and Natural Resins (Pigmos, Rosana Highlands)</span></strong><br /><br /><strong style="color: #0077ff;"><span style="color: #f70000;">Devotion (Active) - A skill to protect your friends. Nullifies all of the enemy's ranged attacks. Available for Pets.</span></strong><br /><strong style="color: #0077ff;"><span style="color: #0047ff;">SLv1 - Obtained from the Class Change to Paladin.<br />SLv2 - Obtained from a Lv.240 Skill Book from Delma in Lograth City.</span></strong><br /><br /><strong style="color: #0077ff;"><span style="color: #f70000;">Guardian (Active) (AoE) - Attack all the enemies around you, making them hostile. Current HP is related to the damage. (You lose 2% of your MaxHP when using this skill, and when attacking a boss or mob with the first hit, it adds a 20% increase in damage but this only works with the first hit.)</span></strong><br /><strong style="color: #0077ff;"><span style="color: #0047ff;">SLv1 - Obtained from a Lv.160 Skill Quest from King Elbano in Capital City Elban. You must:</span><br /><span style="color: #35a700;">-Kill 30 Owlbears and Morays (Inneban Ruins)<br />-Collect 15 Bent Screws (Kriegers and Kanones, Baustelle Sector), 30 Heavy Swords (Orcs, Bizen Forest Sector) and 1 Powerful Engine (Altadora, Baustelle Sector)</span><br /><br /><span style="color: #0047ff;">SLv2 - Obtained from a Lv.200 Skill Quest from Levia in Port Spargas. You must:</span><br /><span style="color: #35a700;">-Kill 50 Crysis, 25 Zlovas and 1 Sianas (Mezzaluna Palace)<br />-Collect 50 Torn Capes (Veldas, Mezzaluna Palace)</span></strong><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #fd0000;">Holy Thrust (Active) - A light element magic attack that is based on your MaxHP. (Adds effect for 4 minutes: ATK +?%, Heal Reward +?%, Item Recovery +?%) (Consumes 40-45% of your MaxMP) (Hidden: Value increased with Knight's Heart. It also adds 20% to the Knight's Heart Bar when used.)</span></strong><br /><strong style="color: #0077ff;"><span style="color: #0047ff;">SLv1 - Obtained from a Lv.140 Skill Quest in Capital City Elban. You must:<br /></span></strong><strong><span style="color: #35a700;">-Collect 1 Corallite (Mars in Lede Salt Lake, Tritonias in Parul Coast or Colabols in Rucao Coast), 5 Light Crystals (Plazuda, Bizen Forest Sector), 10 Powder Snow (Nipasu, Oof Plains) and 15 Light Beads.</span></strong><br /><br /><strong style="color: #0077ff;"><span style="color: #f70000;">Stun Parry (Passive) - Smash enemies while parrying. Chance to knock out an enemy. Lower KO rate for bosses.</span></strong><br /><strong style="color: #0077ff;"><span style="color: #0047ff;">SLv1 - Obtained from a Lv.160 Skill Quest from Levia in Port Spargas. You must:</span><br /><span style="color: #35a700;">-Kill 50 Tengus (Mikasa Gate), Middle Ninjas (Isurugi Temple), Fire Cats (Eccentric's Manor) and Crow Samurais (Amazuki Castle)<br /></span></strong><br /><span style="color: #fd0000;"><strong>Heal Boost (Passive) - Increase magic heal reward. The amount is based on VIT.<br /></strong></span><span style="color: #0047ff;"><strong>SLv1 - Obtained from a Lv.180 Skill Quest from Levia in Port Spargas. You must:<br /></strong></span><span style="color: #35a700;"><strong>-Collect 1 Titanium (Altadora, Baustelle Sector), 20 Jade (Lower Ninjas, Isurugi Temple), 40 Glowing Wings (Meanaes, Baustelle Sector) and 40 Red Metal Fins (Iron Theus, Fort Slebinus)<br /></strong></span><span style="color: #0047ff;"><strong>SLv2 - Obtained from a Lv.300 Skill Quest from King Elbano in Capital City Eldan. You must:<br /></strong></span><span style="color: #35a700;"><strong>-Slay 1 Behemoth (Urslo Sacred Plains) and 40 Soldes (Capital City Gulia)<br />-Collect 5 Colon Hearts (Ivy Colons, Urslo Sacred Plains) and 5 Corallites (Tritonias, Parul Coast)<br /><br /></strong></span><span style="color: #fd0000;"><strong>Fortis (Active) - Increase all elements resistance for a short time. Hate rise and Devotion Rate up. (Consumes 10%? of your MaxHP if in PT)<br /></strong></span><span style="color: #0047ff;"><strong><u>SLv1 - Obtained from a quest from Levia in Port Spargas. You must:<br /></u></strong></span><span style="color: #35a700;"><strong>-Slay 1 Garel (Curiolto) and Rossam (Mt.Holton)<br /></strong></span><strong style="color: #0077ff;"><span style="color: #35a700;">-Collect 20 Mythril and 50 Bent Swords (Artens, The Industrial City of Regus)<br /></span></strong><span style="color: #0047ff;"><strong><u>SLv2 - Obtained from a Lv.200 Skill Book from Filely in Eryldan Desert.<br />SLv3 - Obtained from a Lv.300 Skill Book from Sitara in Kreya City.<br /><br /></u></strong></span><strong><span style="color: #f70000;">Shield Mastery (Passive) - Enhance Parry and Stun Parry by equipping Shields. Nullify damage sometimes. (For a list of shields, look&nbsp;<a href="http://irunaonline.boards.net/thread/25044/list-shields" target="_blank" rel="noopener norewrite">here</a>)</span><br /></strong><span style="color: #0047ff;"><u><strong>SLv1 - Obtained from a Lv.240 Skill Quest from Matif in Drafbourg: Immigrant Ward. You must:<br /></strong></u></span><span style="color: #35a700;"><strong>-Slay 60 Garkins (Isthmus of Kabri) and Oltras (Abbey Ruin)<br /></strong></span><strong><span style="color: #35a700;">-Collect 40 Thin Metal Bits (Masked Soldiers, Dragon Emperor's Palace) and 20 Aqua Auras (Balors, Halib Marshlands)</span><br /><u><span style="color: #0077ff;">SLv2 - Obtained from a Lv.280 Skill Book from Sitara in Kreya City.</span></u><br /></strong><br /><span style="color: #f70000;"><strong>Rage Force (Passive) - Convert Hate into your power. The amount of the hate affects the damage dealt.<br /></strong></span><span style="color: #0047ff;"><strong><u>SLv1 - Obtained from a Lv.220 Skill Quest from Matif in Drafbourg: Immigrant Ward. You must:<br /></u></strong></span><span style="color: #35a700;"><strong>-Collect 70 Fluffy Wings (Stramos, Mt.Jimuy), 30 Scythe-like Claws (Cuppebites, Frontline Base), 10 Greenish Meat (Neknotts, Magonza Fortress) and 1 Odd Red Stone (Beelzedam, Ruins of Zamani)<br /></strong></span><span style="color: #0047ff;"><strong><u>SLv2 - Obtained from a Lv.260 Skill Book from Sitara in Kreya City.<br /><br /></u></strong></span><strong><span style="color: #fd0000;">Divine Aura (Active) - A powerful aura to attract foes. Increase MaxHP, Auto HP Recovery, Hate Rise, Rate Cut and Parry Rate.</span><br /></strong><span style="color: #0047ff;"><strong><u>SLv1 - Obtained from a Lv.220 Skill Quest from Levia in Port Spargas. You must:<br /></u></strong></span><span style="font-weight: bold; color: #35a700;">-Slay 1 Eldas (Divine Tower F4), 40 Fire and Wind Spirits (Divine Tower F3), 40 Earth and Water Spirits (Divine Tower F5)</span><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span style="color: #fd0000;">Job Master (Passive) - Proof of mastering Paladin. Profession bonus increases.</span><br /></span><span style="color: #0047ff; font-weight: bold;"><u>SLv1 - Obtained from a Lv.280 Skill Quest from King Elbano in Capital City Eldan. You must:<br /></u></span><span style="font-weight: bold; color: #35a700;">-Slay 40 Kaimen (Kilf Rocky Area) and 1 Wild Dragon Wilnes (Trial Hall)<br />-Collect 20 Hard Eggs (Ostrias, Tolbas Green District) and 40 Small Dragon Horns (Glew, Bestie Mountain)<br /><br /></span><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span style="color: #fd0000;">Knight's Oath (Active) - Thrust a foe with the power of the Oath. The effect depends on the condition of you and your PT members. (The damage increases the lower your HP is) (Adds Exhaustion Nullification for 5 minutes, cancelling out the Exhaustion effect from Divine Aura and giving back 2% of your MaxHP and MP. Nobody can have ailments on them or else this will not work) (Consumes 100% of Knight's Heart to reduce the time to a 2 second delay)&nbsp;</span><br /></span><span style="color: #0047ff; font-weight: bold;"><u>SLv1 - Obtained from a Lv.260 Skill Quest from Delma in Lograth City. You must:<br /></u></span><span style="color: #35a700;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">-Slay 30 Moss Balls and 1 Death Chils (Sigmy District)</span><br /><span style="font-weight: bold;">-Collect 30 Dirty Scabbards (Goriapes, Mt.Alcado) and Very Hard Stones (Rosa Pitons, Mt.Alcado)</span></span><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #fd0000;">Grand Crusade (Active) -&nbsp;A shield to protect allies. Enhances Devotion and also raises MaxHP. Requires Power Up and Exhaustion Nullification to use. (MaxHP +6% to 1 S.F based on findings) (Adds additional damage to enemy attacks.) (Knight's Heart consumes 50% and enhances the effect.)</span><br /></strong><span style="color: #0047ff;"><strong><u>SLv1 - Obtained from a Skill Quest given by King Elbano in Capital City Eldan. You must:<br /></u></strong></span><span style="color: #35a700;"><strong>-Slay Fallen Angel Ibrie (Ibrie Palace) and 50 Solonias (Fundamental Globe)<br />-Collect 15 Blades of Light (Grandzeas, Meligia Palace) and 30 Hard Claws (Trassis, Leelid's Field)<br /><br /></strong></span><strong style="color: #0077ff;"><span style="color: #fd0000;">Knight's Heart (Passive) -&nbsp;The power given only to the Holy Knight. When hate is gathered, the "Knight's Heart" increases. The effect of a specific skill rises. (Max value of Knight's Heart is 150%.) (Having Knight's Heart enables the following things to happen:</span><br /><span style="color: #0047ff;"><u>SLv1 - Obtained from a Lv.320 Skill Book from Sitara in Kreya City.<br /><br /></u></span><span style="color: #f70000;">Awake (Active) -&nbsp;A skill to maximize your concentration. You are not stunned for a certain amount of times for a short time. (Stun Resistance for 15 seconds, then after effect, an additional 30 seconds. Cannot be reused during this time.) (Prevents Field Stuns)<br /></span><span style="color: #0047ff;"><u>SLv1 - Obtained from a Lv.340 Skill Quest from King Elbano in Capital City Elban. You must:<br /></u></span><span style="color: #35a700;">-Slay 40 Ottos (Dorizora Wasteland) and Cochleas (Mount Nachberg)<br />-Collect 1 Night King Blood Bead (Ster, Mount Nachberg) and 5 Bead Crystals (Easy way to obtain is through Cynthia's quests in Moivan, the Chamber of Moonlight.)<br /><br /></span><span style="color: #f70000;">Shivaku Area (Active) -&nbsp;Tradition technique of the Holy Chivalry. Form the guardian area and take over the damage of allies inside the area. (Attack power is raised in the area for all members.) (Consumes 60% of Knight's Heart)<br /></span><span style="color: #0047ff;"><u>SLv1 - Obtained from a Lv.340 Skill Quest from King Elbano in Capital City Elban. You must:<br /></u></span><span style="color: #35a700;">-Slay 1 Veleno Rosa (Forisco Plains South), 30 Einios (Montalt Forest), Crystaurs (Thelt Forest) and Jiaorongs (Dorizora Wasteland)</span><br /></strong><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></span></span></div>
<div><a></a></div>
<div data-tag="spoiler"><span style="color: #7e9600;">{The Hate Bar, Tips for Parties and Paladin's Roles}</span><span style="color: #0077ff;">{The Hate Bar, Tips for Parties and Paladin's Roles}</span><br /><span style="font-size: x-large;"><span style="color: #b30373;">Throughout the year, one of the notable additions has been the Hate Bar. This bar will change colors and raise if you attack a monster or perform a skill. These colors are very important to follow for Paladins as it is vital for you to keep the Hate with this class so Devotion can work properly and your PT can thrive on getting safer kills through teamwork.</span><br /><span style="color: #b30373;"><img style="max-width: 100%;" src="https://stat.ameba.jp/user_images/20170126/06/emi-riko/2a/70/j/o0480019013853869604.jpg?caw=800" /></span><br /><span style="color: #b30373;">This is the hate bar and it's colors. Pay attention to the bar going from right to left. The right side represents Non aggression, and this is what you should never strive to aim for as the Tank of the PT. Light brown means the mob is not paying their attention to you but they're on the verge of doing it, whereas dark brown means the total opposite. The left side, on the other hand, represents the side of aggression. Always aim for the Pink and Red Colors. These indicate that you are fully in control and everyone in your PT should be alright if Devotion is landing most of the times. Your PT may still die sometimes because Devotion does not have a 100% rate of nullifying AoE attacks, but all of the main damage will be going to you and that will make the Healer's job a lot easier as they do not have to divert their focus on the other members of the PT.</span><br /><u style="color: #b30373;">Now, my tips for Paladin:</u><br /><strong style="color: #b30373;">-The hate bar is not very important when farming weak mobs, but it is important for tankier mobs.</strong><span style="color: #0077ff;">Low HP mobs aren't much of a problem to the PT as they can be handled with ease. However, high HP mobs are a problem and need to be looked after. If you can, communicate with your PT and tell them to let you attack first before they dish out damage.</span><br /><strong style="color: #b30373;">-When there is a continuation effect debuff, your first skill you should be applying to yourself is Devotion.</strong><span style="color: #b30373;"> This is because Devotion helps to nullify AoE attacks and not having this effect on will ensure death on your PT members if they have low health and the boss so happens to use an AoE attack. Applying Devotion will help the PT have more time to get accustomed to what has just happened and adapt to the situation.</span><br /><strong style="color: #b30373;">-You should always carry Consumables and Recovery Items around.</strong><span style="color: #b30373;"> In the case you don't have someone playing the healer role, these items do a great job of playing exactly that role. Paladins are known to be the class that actually should be carrying the most consumables/recovery items of all classes. It just depends on the gears you have, but if you are farming mobs you can switch to an Item Recovery/Item Delay set and use that when you need to heal up. In boss fights, however, the situation will differentiate as you are actively fighting the boss with 0 downtime. Items wise, I think having any item that can delete ailments, increase your resistance or heal you for a good chunk of your HP is great.</span><br /><strong style="color: #b30373;">-Apply buffs only when they matter.</strong><span style="color: #b30373;"> If a boss has an effect wipe, is it worth it to apply the buffs after the fight? There are also some bad PT members that will rush in and won't give you time to apply your buffs. This therefore raises the question above your head. I believe in the case of this, a Paladin should try to adapt and only apply the buffs that are important to the survival of your party.</span><br /><span style="color: #20ca5d;"><u>My tips for other classes that may be reading this:</u><br /><strong>-Do not attack the mob or boss first.</strong> A mob or low HP boss may be okay but attacking the boss first means that Devotion will not work unless the Paladin has the most hate. You are ensuring the lowest survival rate by doing this, and also rendering the Paladin useless by any means.<br /><strong>-Wait during buff time.</strong> I understand that you want to get kills as fast as possible, but this time is really important. Imagine not having revival and then entering into a boss fight wondering how you just died. Well, now you know that it was your fault for not being patient. Paladins need the buffs that affect their HP or resistances as it could be important for hard hitting bosses. You also reap the benefits of whatever buffs may come to you and what you can offer to the PT. This should also be preparation time for the Paladin before going in. If the boss is placed to be close to the player then the Paladin should go in first at all times as bosses are actively aggressive.<br /><strong>Try making a Hate Rise -% Set.</strong> This aids the PT as your skills will not generate much hate at the cost of perhaps some damage, but it could be worth it as the Paladin needs the bar of hate to control the fight. When I fought Sauro 400, there would be times where it would be absolutely difficult to control the hate bar as it fluctuated from pink to brown a countless amount of times due to a speedhack zero ray and non-sh monk fighting for it. It is frustrating and could mean the difference between life and death of the PT. (It has been updated but still!)</span><br /><span style="color: #7e9600;"><u>A Paladin's Roles</u><br />In my opinion, they should mainly be tank as they have the resistance and skills necessary to do this that other classes do not. A healer/support is your best friend.</span></span></div>
